[1] Description
===============================================================================
EduBeam is an educational project to develop a simple, open source structural 
analysis code for beams and frames.

[2] Authors
===============================================================================
The following people have contributed to EduBeam development.

Borek Patzak (original author, lead developer)
Jan Stransky (element loadings, windows installation)
Vit Smilauer 

[3] What is here
===============================================================================
The directory tree below holds source code to the EduBeam package. 

EduBeam_TOP_DIR - contains source code of the EduBeam package
|
|-- examples - contains examples and tests

[4] Pre-requisites
===============================================================================
The EduBeam requires the python3 interpreter. The following libraries work 
on Linux (some downloaded directly, rather than via pip or package manager):
PyOpenGL (3.1.0)
numpy (1.15.1)
wxPython (4.0.1)
minidom

[5] Running EduBeam examples
===============================================================================
Just open (In main menu follow File->Open) one of the example files provided.

Bugs
==============================================================================

Please mail all bug reports and suggestions to [info@oofem.org]. I will try to
give satisfaction, if the time is at least partially on my side. 


                                Enjoy
                                        Borek Patzak
